<i>This is Rick Dees.</i>

00:44.819 --> 00:49.779
<i>If you want a song played,</i>
<i>call the radio station right now.</i>

00:51.960 --> 00:55.987
<i>You park in an abandoned lot.</i>
<i>You attend the movie.</i>

00:56.297 --> 01:01.030
<i>You come out to find that thieves</i>
<i>have ripped off your stereo.</i>

01:07.108 --> 01:09.167
<i>This wouldn't have happened...</i>

01:09.377 --> 01:14.679
<i>...if you'd purchased the</i>
<i>James Brown auto alarm! Listen!</i>

01:19.520 --> 01:24.856
<i>The James Brown auto alarm,</i>
<i>scattering thieves near and far!</i>

01:25.493 --> 01:27.654
<i>The James Brown auto alarm.</i>

01:27.996 --> 01:30.362
<i>Get yours today!</i>

02:32.060 --> 02:33.925
What are you doing?

02:34.262 --> 02:36.594
-Here.
-Oh, never mind.

02:42.303 --> 02:43.895
Morning.

02:48.910 --> 02:50.605
Coffee.

02:54.916 --> 02:58.545
What time did you go home
last night, 3:00 a.m.?

02:58.753 --> 03:01.881
You look like you've been
in a plane crash.

03:02.090 --> 03:07.460
-This may shock you, but humans sleep.
-I know, I know.

03:08.463 --> 03:12.991
Gruen gave me a big project.
I think it's some kind of test.

03:13.267 --> 03:17.465
Where's my depreciation schedule?
I've lost my deprec--

03:18.406 --> 03:21.432
I think I have everything.
Profit plan...

03:22.610 --> 03:24.168
...flow charts....

03:24.445 --> 03:28.142
-How much time do I have?
-Four minutes.

03:29.951 --> 03:31.851
Walter.

03:33.621 --> 03:37.455
-You should wind down.
-I'm getting something out of it.

03:39.594 --> 03:42.722
You won't believe
what happened last night.

03:42.930 --> 03:46.093
You worked on your presentation?
Not at all?

03:46.300 --> 03:48.700
I had drinks at The Blue Dragon--

03:48.936 --> 03:51.871
Don't tell me one of your sex stories.

03:52.106 --> 03:57.169
-Bringing the embalmer tonight?
-She's not an embalmer. She does hair.

03:57.411 --> 04:02.644
-No. I have a date with a gorgeous--
-In the parking lot of the club...

04:02.850 --> 04:06.377
...I see this woman,
maybe 35, kind of classy.

04:06.654 --> 04:11.751
I figure she's waiting for her car.
So, what the hell, I talk to her.

04:12.126 --> 04:17.358
Turns out, she came in a limo. I say,
''I've never been in a limo before.''

04:17.565 --> 04:21.968
She stares at me for 30 seconds,
then says, ''Let's take a ride.''

04:22.170 --> 04:27.608
In the limo, she pushes a button and
a wall's up between us and the driver.

04:27.809 --> 04:31.267
She hits another button,
a sunroof opens.

04:31.479 --> 04:34.141
Bar slides open.

04:34.348 --> 04:38.148
She pours us vodka,
plays Sly and the Family Stone.

04:38.352 --> 04:41.480
Next thing I know, we slide onto PCH.

04:45.193 --> 04:48.959
Full moon, 2:00 a.m,
vodka, limo, music.

04:49.163 --> 04:50.994
And I'm thinking....

04:51.666 --> 04:54.430
-I don't believe you.
-We start to kiss.

04:54.669 --> 04:58.935
I slide my hand up her dress.
What do I find? Garter belt!

04:59.140 --> 05:03.474
-All your women wear garter belts!
-So I tell her I want her...

05:03.678 --> 05:08.411
...from behind, standing up,
with my head sticking out the sunroof.

05:08.616 --> 05:10.140
So we start doing it.

05:10.351 --> 05:14.378
We're going 60, my head's out
the roof, my hair's flying....

05:14.622 --> 05:19.559
This didn't happen. There was
no limo, no woman, no sunroof--

05:21.829 --> 05:23.296
That's disgusting.

05:23.497 --> 05:28.525
I'm ashamed to know you. How do you
get women to do these things?

05:29.103 --> 05:34.234
As you know by now, Yakamoto has
agreed to entrust the management...

05:34.442 --> 05:38.435
...of all his personal
and corporate assets to us.

05:38.646 --> 05:42.082
No small thanks
to the efforts of Harry Gruen.

05:43.284 --> 05:46.276
I'm sure Mr. Yakamoto's
confidence in us...

05:46.487 --> 05:51.117
...will increase with the lethal charm
you'll all exude tonight.

05:51.359 --> 05:53.327
A word of caution.

05:53.661 --> 05:57.654
He's very traditional.
Old-fashioned ideas about women.

05:57.865 --> 06:00.231
Wives must follow certain rules.

06:00.434 --> 06:05.872
Can't speak until spoken to, don't sit
until he does, all that crap.

06:07.275 --> 06:09.004
Meanwhile...

06:09.277 --> 06:13.179
...he keeps a stable of concubines
you wouldn't believe.

06:17.718 --> 06:19.015
Anyway...

06:20.454 --> 06:23.389
...this is a very old-world guy.

06:23.591 --> 06:28.756
So watch yourselves, and keep
your wives away from the mai tais.

06:28.963 --> 06:32.922
Okay, a few facts
about the man. Denny...

06:33.134 --> 06:36.297
...show us Yakamoto's
holdings for '85.

06:38.205 --> 06:42.938
Damn. Spreadsheets are still printing.
Machine's been down.

06:44.245 --> 06:47.703
Okay, forget it.
Walter, let's have your report.

07:00.161 --> 07:05.292
Yakamoto Worldwide has shown almost
recession-proof capabilities.

07:05.499 --> 07:09.162
Even in a disastrous third quarter...

07:10.071 --> 07:12.062
...his fish oil conglomerate...

07:12.306 --> 07:16.174
...bolstered his net worth
by some 27%.

07:23.484 --> 07:27.614
Walter, you look like shit.
Where were you last night?

07:27.822 --> 07:29.289
I was here until 3.

07:29.490 --> 07:33.290
This is the money business.
Image is everything.

07:33.494 --> 07:36.463
Look at you. This jacket is shit.

07:36.664 --> 07:41.624
See, men like Yakamoto don't make
deals with the lint man, here.

07:41.836 --> 07:45.670
-Now look at Denny. That's a suit.
-Armani, sir.

07:45.873 --> 07:48.364
-Take a few tips from him.
-Yes, sir.

07:48.609 --> 07:53.103
We'll make a good assistant
portfolio assessor out of you yet.

07:53.314 --> 07:54.975
See you at dinner.

07:56.484 --> 07:59.112
-Who's he bringing?
-I don't know, sir.

07:59.320 --> 08:02.016
God, I hope it's not the embalmer.

08:21.976 --> 08:24.376
-Can I borrow your wife?
-Sure. $50.

08:24.578 --> 08:27.411
I'm serious.
Denise bagged out on me.

08:27.648 --> 08:31.607
I need a date. They don't know
Susie's my sister-in-law.

08:31.819 --> 08:35.152
She'd do it, but it's our anniversary.

08:35.356 --> 08:37.688
-Going to Spago's.
-I'm ruined.

08:37.892 --> 08:40.986
Watch this. This guy 'll make an offer.

08:41.195 --> 08:44.653
-Have you decided?
-I can't go higher than 15,500.

08:44.899 --> 08:47.197
No can do. It's 17,000 list.

08:47.401 --> 08:50.097
What? You told me it was 18,000 list!

08:50.371 --> 08:55.502
You made $1 000 off your brother? I'm
bankrolling your dinner at Spago's!

08:55.743 --> 08:57.870
Stop it. You're scaring him.

08:58.079 --> 09:02.573
You're scaring me. Jesus, you'd
cheat your own flesh and blood.

09:02.783 --> 09:04.375
We'll talk.

09:06.253 --> 09:09.745
-I'll make it up to you.
-You'll write me a check?

09:09.957 --> 09:12.187
No, but I know this fantastic--

09:12.426 --> 09:16.760
Stop! You're gonna recommend
one of your psychotic friends.

09:16.964 --> 09:19.023
I resent that, Walter.

09:19.233 --> 09:24.535
You've set me up before, only you
forget to mention one crucial detail:

09:24.738 --> 09:29.072
She's a dopehead, a lesbian,
keeps dead cats in the freezer....

09:29.276 --> 09:33.303
What a New Year's!
''The champagne's in the icebox.''

09:33.547 --> 09:38.450
I'm sorry. Seriously, I know someone.
Nadia Gates, Susie's cousin.

09:38.652 --> 09:43.214
-Ted, I don't want to hear it.
-Don't you trust your own brother?

09:43.457 --> 09:47.393
No argument there.
But, no bullshit, Nadia's amazing.

09:47.628 --> 09:49.755
She's just moved back to town...

09:49.964 --> 09:53.058
-...and wants to meet people!
-What's she like?

09:53.267 --> 09:57.499
She's a sweetheart, good sense
of humour. You'll love her!

09:57.738 --> 10:01.504
I won't love her
because this won't happen!

10:01.742 --> 10:05.143
Suit yourself.
But I highly recommend her.

10:05.346 --> 10:07.576
Talk about the kiss of death!

10:10.284 --> 10:14.846
-Call us if you change your mind.
-I won't!

10:20.461 --> 10:23.021
Hi. Is Chloe there?

10:23.998 --> 10:26.831
Do you have the rifle range's number?

10:27.034 --> 10:31.971
Never mind. Look, I'll just
call her later. Thanks.

10:53.227 --> 10:55.695
<i>-Hello?</i>
-Is she reasonably pretty?

10:56.897 --> 10:59.957
''Reasonably'' doesn't begin
to describe it.

11:00.167 --> 11:04.968
I'm looking at her picture now.
She's an honest-to-God knockout.

11:05.706 --> 11:08.869
Ted, just this once, please.
The truth.

11:09.376 --> 11:12.903
Susie, tell Walter Nadia's pretty.

11:13.180 --> 11:15.410
She's very pretty, Walter.

11:18.586 --> 11:21.646
-When was the picture taken?
<i>-Four years ago.</i>

11:21.889 --> 11:25.985
Four years? She could've been
disfigured in four years!

11:26.193 --> 11:30.425
-She could've gained 100 pounds!
-She's gorgeous! Stop it!

11:30.664 --> 11:32.256
I almost forgot!

11:32.499 --> 11:36.026
Don't get her drunk.
She loses control completely.

11:36.670 --> 11:39.605
But don't get her drunk. If you do...

11:39.840 --> 11:42.741
...she loses control!

11:43.210 --> 11:46.737
Loses her inhibitions,
or she pees on the floor?

11:47.348 --> 11:49.373
What's ''lose control'' mean?

11:49.583 --> 11:52.552
Oh, you know, she gets real wild.

11:53.454 --> 11:56.855
She gets real wild!

12:02.062 --> 12:06.863
All right! I may kill you later,
but I'm doing this now...

12:07.067 --> 12:09.160
...before I change my mind.
Give me the number.

12:23.917 --> 12:26.750
-Walter?
-Yeah.

12:27.888 --> 12:29.412
Come on in.

12:37.331 --> 12:39.390
I'll just be a minute.

12:43.437 --> 12:47.339
I hope you don't mind
helping me with my suitcase.

12:47.574 --> 12:51.670
I'm moving out of here.
I'll be staying with a friend.

12:53.013 --> 12:56.915
If you feel like it,
a friend's having an art exhibit.

12:57.117 --> 13:01.144
If we have time before dinner,
maybe we could go?

13:01.355 --> 13:03.346
Yeah, no problem.

13:03.757 --> 13:07.249
Well, here goes, Walter. Ready or not.

13:07.461 --> 13:11.488
Oh, damn it!
This has been going on all night.

13:12.032 --> 13:15.365
There may be some matches over there.

13:16.036 --> 13:17.970
Let me look.

13:18.639 --> 13:20.664
It may be over there.

13:21.675 --> 13:22.972
Here.

13:24.111 --> 13:28.946
Now this is a blind date.
Here's your chance to run for it.

13:30.184 --> 13:32.744
Your very last chance.

13:35.522 --> 13:37.752
You missed your chance.

13:44.498 --> 13:45.795
I'm glad.

14:04.718 --> 14:07.380
I had no idea.

14:09.289 --> 14:11.348
Do you know this artist?

14:12.393 --> 14:16.295
I've met him once.
He's Susie's friend.

14:16.530 --> 14:20.057
I mean, coming was her idea.
We can go.

14:20.501 --> 14:23.993
-I don't have any obligation to him.
-No, come on.

14:24.204 --> 14:26.365
We're both adults, aren't we?

14:27.141 --> 14:29.302
I thought I was.

14:30.177 --> 14:33.010
I don't know. Maybe I'm not now.

14:35.682 --> 14:37.741
Can I ask you something?

14:39.820 --> 14:41.754
Yeah, I guess so.

14:42.823 --> 14:47.988
Why didn't you have a date tonight?
Is there something I should know?

14:48.195 --> 14:52.996
I can't imagine why you don't
have a date every night of the week.

14:53.233 --> 14:56.600
Know what? I was thinking
the same about you.

14:56.837 --> 15:01.171
-Come on, I'm serious.
-Me too. I was thinking that.

15:03.544 --> 15:05.739
I asked you first.

15:10.717 --> 15:13.743
I stopped dating
about three months ago.

15:14.021 --> 15:16.751
I was involved,
but it didn't work out.

15:16.957 --> 15:22.224
Boy, how it didn't work out. So I was
living in Baton Rouge with my mama.

15:22.596 --> 15:26.794
And you're my first date.
But you almost weren't.

15:27.067 --> 15:29.297
Susie talked me into it...

15:30.070 --> 15:32.038
...I'm glad to say.

15:33.207 --> 15:34.970
So how about you?

15:36.643 --> 15:40.773
Well, my date backed out
at the last minute...

15:41.215 --> 15:43.308
...I'm glad to say.

15:49.223 --> 15:51.214
You want some candy?

15:52.292 --> 15:54.783
I'm not much of a candy person.

15:55.762 --> 15:59.163
That's good.
I always was a candy person.

15:59.433 --> 16:03.733
Some people drink,
some people do drugs. I do sugar.

16:07.307 --> 16:09.571
This looks Japanese.

16:11.445 --> 16:14.141
''Master and Concubines''?

16:15.516 --> 16:17.484
It's Yakamoto.

16:17.751 --> 16:20.948
-What is?
-The big business dinner tonight...

16:21.154 --> 16:25.056
...is for this Japanese industrialist
new client of ours.

16:25.259 --> 16:29.127
He's old-world Japanese.
His wife's like his slave...

16:29.329 --> 16:31.320
...and he keeps concubines.

16:31.532 --> 16:35.263
-You're kidding.
-No. His wife knows all about it.

16:35.502 --> 16:37.936
It's traditional or something.

16:39.973 --> 16:43.636
Tell me something.
Are you into those traditions?

16:43.844 --> 16:49.009
No, I'm actually a
one-concubine kind of guy...

16:49.683 --> 16:51.207
-...actually.
-Good.

16:52.286 --> 16:56.689
So, what was it that made you
break up with this guy?

16:56.890 --> 17:00.018
-What do you mean?
-What was he like?

17:00.227 --> 17:02.661
-Psychopath. Like that guy over there.
-What's wrong?

17:04.464 --> 17:08.366
That's him! That's my psychotic
ex-boyfriend David.

17:08.868 --> 17:11.736
There. The guy in the goofy bow tie.

17:12.005 --> 17:13.632
He looks okay to me.

17:13.839 --> 17:17.674
He's been chasing me
for three months. I moved twice.

17:17.944 --> 17:22.608
I think he's coming over here!
Watch it. Please just hide.

17:22.816 --> 17:24.374
Just relax.

17:28.789 --> 17:30.347
Hello, Nadia.

17:30.557 --> 17:34.493
-David, don't start anything.
-I just want to say hello.

17:34.728 --> 17:36.320
Hi, I'm David.

17:36.530 --> 17:39.693
-Walter.
-She has every reason to be upset.

17:39.900 --> 17:43.666
I was so in love,
I made a total asshole of myself.

17:43.870 --> 17:46.896
Apology accepted.
Nice to meet you.

17:47.140 --> 17:50.632
-How long you been dating?
-None of your business!

17:50.877 --> 17:55.246
It is my business.
There's not a night that's gone by--

17:55.515 --> 17:58.814
You son of a bitch,
are you drilling her?!

17:59.019 --> 18:01.510
Shut up and leave her alone!

18:03.190 --> 18:06.421
Wait, I want to talk to you.
I'll find you!

18:12.899 --> 18:16.335
-I have an idea.
-Yeah? What?

18:20.941 --> 18:22.841
Thank you.

18:34.354 --> 18:38.256
-Okay, Walter, what's going on?
-Well....

18:38.625 --> 18:41.753
We have about half an hour.
Indulge me.

19:13.460 --> 19:17.226
-You like guitar?
-Oh, yeah, I do.

19:18.732 --> 19:22.725
<i>-We're set. How's the level for you?</i>
-It's basically cool.

19:22.936 --> 19:27.134
Turn up the monitors a bit
and we'll be there. Thanks.

19:27.340 --> 19:30.400
-How are you?
-Good, Stanley. How are you?

19:30.977 --> 19:33.138
Did you bring your guitar?

19:34.748 --> 19:38.013
No, I brought something better
than a guitar.

19:39.319 --> 19:41.583
-How you doing?
-Hi, how are you?

19:41.822 --> 19:43.551
Good, good.

19:45.525 --> 19:49.188
You ever hear him play?
He's really fantastic.

19:52.365 --> 19:53.992
Relax...

19:54.501 --> 19:56.901
...sip a little champagne.

19:59.239 --> 20:01.935
I don't think I should drink.

20:03.043 --> 20:05.910
The last three or four times I ...

20:06.113 --> 20:09.605
I mean, it sort of makes me go crazy!

20:12.018 --> 20:16.717
Well, one little glass
isn't gonna make you go crazy.

20:22.963 --> 20:25.261
This is our first toast.

20:26.099 --> 20:29.432
To auspicious beginnings.

20:35.542 --> 20:37.203
It's really good.

20:37.410 --> 20:41.107
<i>Stanley Jordan, take two. Rolling.</i>

20:59.266 --> 21:02.429
So, what made you think
to stop by here?

21:04.304 --> 21:09.071
I recorded here when I thought
I wanted to be a musician.

21:10.010 --> 21:14.242
I played guitar. But I really
don't have time for it now.

21:15.515 --> 21:20.976
I played all the time. I went to
the bathroom carrying a Stratocaster.

21:21.188 --> 21:24.919
I drove my mom nuts.
I got tendinitis.

21:27.961 --> 21:29.929
Why did you give it up?

21:30.997 --> 21:32.464
Well....

21:34.601 --> 21:37.934
Because if you want
to be a musician...

21:38.138 --> 21:43.132
...you're guaranteeing yourself
a life of poverty and obscurity...

21:43.343 --> 21:46.176
...unless you're talented
like Stanley.

21:47.380 --> 21:48.472
And...

21:49.516 --> 21:51.507
...I got a good job now...

21:51.818 --> 21:55.811
...good car. Next year,
I'll be able to get a condo.

21:57.824 --> 21:59.155
I don't know.

21:59.860 --> 22:01.987
It just kind of made sense.

22:05.265 --> 22:08.462
We're gonna be late.
Let me give you a little--

22:14.808 --> 22:17.208
Oh, I'm getting bad.

22:17.777 --> 22:20.769
I'm starting to feel the champagne.

22:24.184 --> 22:25.947
That's okay.

22:26.152 --> 22:27.881
Feel away.

22:28.321 --> 22:29.481
Come on.

23:10.697 --> 23:14.155
Hi, I called for Davis,
for two, please.

23:14.935 --> 23:18.336
-Joseph, table six.
-Follow me, please.

23:18.538 --> 23:23.373
Please don't touch the flowers.
The arrangement is very expensive.

23:23.576 --> 23:27.910
These things don't smell.
They're no good anyway.

23:29.683 --> 23:32.948
-Sorry. Oh, my God.
-It's all right.

23:33.219 --> 23:35.414
-You sure?
-It 'll be fine.

23:47.901 --> 23:50.301
-Lovely-looking girl.
-Thank you.

23:50.537 --> 23:52.562
-You know my wife.
-Yes, hello.

23:52.772 --> 23:55.468
Very nice to meet you, Mrs. Gruen.

24:01.147 --> 24:05.709
Thank you. Do you think you could
find me some safety pins?

24:05.952 --> 24:07.783
Safety pins?

24:07.988 --> 24:10.252
No, I don't think so.

24:11.224 --> 24:13.749
There's a lot of roast beef in here.

24:13.960 --> 24:17.623
Would you care for a cocktail?

24:17.831 --> 24:22.325
-A bottle of your finest champagne.
-Very good.

24:22.602 --> 24:24.001
Thank you.

24:26.573 --> 24:28.404
Oh, my God.

24:29.943 --> 24:31.171
That's Yakamoto.

24:34.147 --> 24:35.671
Good evening.

24:36.249 --> 24:40.185
-My wife.
-Very nice to meet you, Mr. Yakimoto.

24:40.420 --> 24:42.354
Yakamoto.

24:44.591 --> 24:46.582
Mrs. Yakamoto.

24:47.127 --> 24:49.994
-How lovely you look.
-Thank you.

24:51.297 --> 24:55.666
That's incredible.
She's like a geisha girl.

25:11.951 --> 25:16.820
Cupcake, would you excuse me
for just a minute?

25:17.690 --> 25:19.282
Business.

25:24.130 --> 25:27.031
-They still do that in Japan?
-I don't know--

25:27.300 --> 25:30.531
Walter, you old dog.

25:31.538 --> 25:35.201
-Denny Gordon, this is Nadia Gates.
-How do you do?

25:35.475 --> 25:39.343
-Hi.
-I gotta hand it to you.

25:39.546 --> 25:43.573
This is the most exciting
woman in the place.

25:43.817 --> 25:46.945
Thank you. Nice tie.
Where did you get it?

25:47.153 --> 25:51.817
I don't remember. Probably
one of those places over on Rodeo.

25:52.058 --> 25:55.994
-Where's that?
-You don't know where Rodeo is?

25:56.196 --> 25:59.927
No, I know where it is.
I just wondered if you did.

26:03.169 --> 26:05.603
What happened to your pocket?

26:05.905 --> 26:09.534
-Oh, we had a little--
-That's the new style.

26:12.078 --> 26:14.546
See? Oh, that looks nice.

26:15.782 --> 26:20.583
-Aren't you forgetting your date?
-My date? Oh, right. Yes.

